Read all about the Grinder:
http://grinder.sourceforge.net/

Download The Grinder.

Copy the .example files, e.g.
cp setGrinderEnv.sh.example setGrinderEnv.sh

Edit them to reflect your system configuration. 
You probably only have to edit setGrinderEnv.sh to reflect the grinder and java installation paths.

Make the scripts writable:
chmod +x *.sh

cp grinder.properties.example grinder.properties

You can edit grinder.properties if you like/must:
http://grinder.sourceforge.net/g3/properties.html

Now start the console:
./startConsole.sh

Start an agent (in another terminal session):
./startAgent.sh

